Hydra
=====

Hydra is a lightweight tabbed browser built using GTK+-2.0 and the WebKit rendering engine. It aims to be a complete replacement for larger, more resource intensive browsers, such as Firefox and Google Chrome.

Features
--------

The main features of Hydra include:
- tabs
- advanced search & highlighting
- favicons
- download support

Dependencies
------------

Hydra requires WebKitGTK 1.0 and GTK+ 2.0 or above.

Keyboard Shortcuts
------------------

CTRL + j = go forward
CTRL + k = go back
CTRL + PageUp = switch to previous tab
CTRL + PageDown = switch to next tab
CTRL + t = new tab
CTRL + w = close tab
CTRL + n = new window
CTRL + q = close window
CTRL + + = zoom in
CTRL + - = zoom out
CTRL + 0 = reset zoom
CTRL + r = reload page
CTRL + enter = search URL bar contents with search engine (google as default)
CTRL + f = open search bar
CTRL + h = open history with dmenu
CTRL + g = opens history and launches url in new tab 'tab and go'
ALT + enter + find bar = reverse searchs
Escape = return focus to page, hide searchbar if focused

